      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A p0171 code indicating running lean could be a sign of a few things. First, let's check the fuel pressure. If it's low, it could be due to a clogged fuel filter or a failing fuel pump. Next, inspect the fuel injectors for proper operation. If they're not delivering the right amount of fuel, it could cause lean running. Lastly, check the mass airflow sensor (MAF) again for debris or damage, as it can also affect the fuel mixture. If the MAF is fine, you might want to look at the throttle body and its connections for any leaks or blockages.",
